shared_text:
White Oak High School
August 26 at 7:57 PM ·

The following is a message from Mr. Brian Gray, Superintendent:

White Oak ISD Community,

While it is difficult to predict the weather, due to Hurricane Laura, I am concerned about the possibility of heavy rain and wind tomorrow morning (Thursday) when our route buses will be on the road, along with the real possibility of an extended power outage on one or more campuses. After consultation with local officials and other area school districts, White Oak ISD has determined that it is the best interest of safety that we close school tomorrow, Thursday, August 27. We wanted to send this out tonight so that parents would have an opportunity to make any arrangements necessary. We apologize for any inconvenience.

Thank you for your continued support of White Oak ISD

REMINDER: Online registration is open. Please log in to your Skyward account to complete. All current students MUST register in order to attend White Oak ISD. post_text:
To our White Oak ISD Community:

Superintendent Brian Gray, district and campus leadership teams, and the Board of Trustees are working hard on school re-opening plans. We are currently evaluating all options and survey responses along with TEA and CDC guidelines to determine the best steps forward. We plan to release information to our parents by the end of the week. We will also have information regarding those that want to utilize the "in-home" option.

We are working diligently to make sure that we look at every safety option for students and staff during these challenging and fluid times. Thank you for your continued support and patience.

The staff at White Oak Middle School want to know how you are doing so join us in a Zoom Meeting. Middle School students need to check their email and/or Google Classroom for an invitation to join their teachers and administrators for a ZOOM meeting. The login and password will be included in the invitation.

This time will be spent on checking in with each other and answer any questions students may have. Each grade level will ZOOM once a week while the school is closed. I look forward to "seeing" all of you!

6th Grade- Mondays at 10:00
7th Grade- Wednesdays at 3:00
8th Grade- Thursdays at 3:00

Hi Class of 2023 and Parents,

post_text:
White Oak ISD will be hosting a free dinner for all Veterans and Active Duty Military Personnel this Friday night, November 9th. The meal will be served at 6 pm in the Secondary Food Service building. Please come and bring your spouse as our guest for a nice meal and plenty of time to fellowship with others in the community.

We are also asking our parents and staff members to help get the word out concerning this event. If you know someone who has served or is serving currently, please extend this invitation on behalf of all of us at White Oak ISD.

The Board of Trustees, faculty and staff at White Oak are grateful for the service and sacrifice of our service men and women! It will be our pleasure to provide this small token of our appreciation.

post_text:
Shuttle Service for Homecoming Game Parking

In anticipation of a large crowd for Friday night’s game with Winnsboro, White Oak ISD will provide shuttle service to the stadium from two locations in town. Citizens National Bank (1101 S White Oak Rd, White Oak) and White Oak City Hall (906 S White Oak Rd, White Oak) have graciously offered their parking lots as overflow for the game.

If you park at either location, a White Oak School Bus will pick you up and drop you off at the Old Middle School Gym. If you or a family member is unable to walk down the hill, we will also have a smaller bus that can drop off at the ticket gate.

There will be a sign designating the pick up point at each location
Shuttle service will begin at 6:30 pm and continue until kickoff.
Shuttle service will resume in the middle of the 4th quarter and continue for 30 minutes after the end of the game.

Thank you and we hope you enjoy Homecoming 2018 at White Oak High School!

shared_text:
Kristin Koonce‎White Oak Ex-Student's Association.
September 25, 2018 at 8:14 PM · White Oak, TX ·

*PLEASE SHARE*

HEY, ROUGHNECKS! WE HAVE SOME VERY, VERY EXCITING NEWS!

Coach Boyett has WRITTEN A BOOK!

It's called "Coach With A Purpose" and it features 32 topical chapters of insight based on a 25 year tenure as the Head Basketball Coach at White Oak High School in White Oak, TX as well as features on White Oak's 2012 & 2013 State Championship teams and individual profiles of all 111 alumni from 1992-2016!

It's beneficial to all coaches who strive to make an impact on their athletes on and off the court or field.

It's available ONLINE ONLY and you can purchase it here: http://www.lulu.com/shop/ron-boyett/coach-with-a-purpose/paperback/product-23811541.html

Please help us spread the word by SHARING THIS POST to your own page and tagging ANY & ALL White Oak Roughneck basketball players!

I BELIEVE!

We are ready to see our 6th-8th graders tomorrow!! Here are a few things to remember:

Make sure you drive the appropriate speed in the school zone- no texting while driving.

Be patient!!!
Student pick up areas- in front of cafeteria, across the street at the crosswalk, behind the building, Pick up IS NOT ALLOWED in the front drive- this is for buses only.
Have your child at school by 7:50. Tardy bell rings at 7:55.
We are looking forward to another great year at WOMS!

post_text:
Migration Mysteries Invitation

Who: Parents of 6th graders are invited!
What: Students will present to the City of White Oak Parks Department.
When: May 1st during your child’s English class period
Where: Middle School Think Lab

Parents and anyone with a vested interest in your child,

You are invited to see your child present their findings to the question: How can White Oak Parks Department protect and preserve migratory species for future generations?
During the month of April, all 6th graders have been conducting research on migratory species in order to learn how organisms interact within their ecosystem. Students have prepared a multimedia presentation with their solutions to the driving question. On May 1st, students will present their findings to Joe Theriot, a representative of the City of White Oak.
Please join us Tuesday, May 1st during your child’s English class time to see them propose their plans!

Thank you,
Coach Bohn and Mrs. Kelley

post_text:
Active Shooter Response Training

The Board of Trustees at White Oak ISD invites the community of White Oak to Active Shooter Response Training. The event will take place in the CC Simmons Auditorium on Sunday, March 11, 2018. The event will begin at 2:30 pm and end by 4:30 pm including a Q&A time at the end of the presentation.

The trainer will be Mark Seguin, TBG Solutions Inc. Tyler Texas. He recently provided training to all employees at White Oak ISD and we feel his message and insight will be beneficial to everyone in White Oak.

There will be an updated report by the district on the security measures in place at WOISD and our commitment to providing a safe learning environment for our students, faculty and staff.

On behalf of the District, I hope to see you next Sunday.

Michael Gilbert

White Oak Schools

post_text:
On Friday evening, February 16, 2018, a picture was posted on the web that threatened harm to our school system. This threat was taken very seriously and White Oak PD took swift action to investigate the validity of the threat. By mid-morning, Saturday, February 17th, it was determined the threat was not real. Instead, it was a very ill-advised “prank” that led to a heightened level of concern for the District Leadership Team, White Oak PD and many members of the community.

Rest assured that this situation was handled swiftly, thoroughly and with the extreme level of concern merited by the message/picture sent. For those in the community that notified officials to raise this concern, Thank You for your action and level of awareness that allowed this to be handled in the appropriate manner.

Michael Gilbert
White Oak ISD

There will be a new traffic pattern around the High School to accommodate a construction zone in the north student parking lot (in red). Please take the time to review the map included in the message and make not of the following:
There will be no through traffic in front of the high school and parking in that area will be for teachers only. (in yellow)
Areas available for student parking are outlined in orange. Those that park across the street from the auditorium will have a crossing guard to ensure safe passage to campuses.
All High School student drop-off and pick-up will be in front of the Food Service building and traffic is designated as one way from south to north (in green). **(Traffic coming from the north on White Oak Road are encouraged to drop-off in the parking lot across the street and use the protected cross walk)
This traffic pattern will be in place until the end of August 2018. The district would like to thank you in advance for your cooperation and patience during the process of upgrading our facilities.

Beginning Monday morning, December 4, 2017, Roughneck Drive will be reduced to one lane in front of the football stadium. Two lane operation will resume at the end of the Home Side Bleachers. Temporary fencing will be in place to designate the construction site. This is necessary to allow for the construction zone at the new Field House Site. This traffic pattern will remain in place until September of 2018.
We have included an image of the traffic pattern for your benefit. It can also be viewed on the main page of the district's website, www.woisd.net.
White Oak ISD would like to thank you in advance for your patience and cooperation during this time of district improvement projects.

post_text:
Help us send a love gift to help Tennessee recover from devastating wildfires.
This year the Roughneck Book Club partnered with the Medina Middle School Book Club in Medina, TN. We love our Tennessee friends and want to help them in this time of need. Even though our friends in Medina are not directly affected by the wildfires, many towns in Eastern Tennessee are in danger. Please help us send a love gift to help them recover.
You may donate money or gift cards until December 9, 2016.
You may drop off money or gift cards to the White Oak Middle School office or give to any Roughneck Book Club member. If you have any questions, please call or email Mrs. Cooper.
903.291.2058
cooperm@woisd.net
https://www.smore.com/bqs77

Common Sense Certified School- Digital Citizenship

We are pleased to announce that White Oak Middle School has been named a Common Sense Certified School! We believe that digital citizenship skills have become essential to students as we use technology to transform learning. We are committed to teaching our students how to think critically, behave safely, and make smart decisions in the digital world.

This is the itinerary for the 6th grade Band Trip

7:20 a.m. – Meet in the MS Band Hall, Dressed for the Contest. Everyone should dress NICELY! We will check roll, and then load the buses for Canton.

8:40: Arrive in Canton

8:50: Warm up

9:05 – Performance

9:30 – Go to Water-park

2:00 – Depart Splash Kingdom

3:15 – Return to White Oak. (Times are approximate. Please be flexible.)

*Remember, there will be a locker room for everyone to change into their swim suit. They have lockers for rent. There will be a large number of kids there, so everyone is responsible for their clothes, money, and anything else that they bring into the Water-park.

** Every student gets a free lunch once we get to the water park. If they want anything else, they need to bring money.

***Parents and students stay up to date while on the band trip. Text this message: @dbk8g to this number. 81010

(Presidents’ Day, officially Washington’s Birthday, is a federal holiday observed on the third Monday of February in honor of George Washington, born on February 22. The holiday is popularly recognized as honoring also Abraham Lincoln, born on February 12, and sometimes all the U.S. Presidents.

post_text:
This coming Monday, January 18 is a school holiday. (Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. Day is a federal holiday honoring the achievements of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr., the chief spokesman for nonviolent activism in the civil rights movement to end racial segregation. It is observed on the third Monday of January each year, which is close to January 15, Dr. King's birthday.)

White Oak ISD has scheduled 4 early release days this year for staff development. Our next early release day is Wednesday, January 27. On that day, middle school students will be dismissed at 12:00 pm. Bus transportation will be provided. (Our final early release for staff development will be February 24)
